question: Baffin Island, Victoria Island, Ellesmere Island is geographically associated with which nation?
explanation: Baffin Island, Victoria Island, Ellesmere Island are the islands located in Canada. Ellesmere Island is a part of the Queen Elizabeth Islands of the Arctic Archipelago. It is Canada's third-largest island. It is famous for the Arctic Willow vegetation. Baffin Island is the largest island in Canada. Victoria Island is the second-largest island.
